      "message": "hmm, I don\u0027t really think this is a good idea:\n1. quite a few operations are done in the loader code itself, and this callback only gets added after that. So it misses quite a few cases\n2. this will also invalidate snapshots because of all crashes whatsoever, including GPU-related ones. The better option would be to have a \"crash counter\" in the snapshot\u0027s protobuf and only invalidate it if we\u0027ve crashed couple times with no successful runs in between; also if the crash is in ~2+ minutes after the loading (or RamLoader\u0027s completed its background loading) we can assume it\u0027s not related to the snapshot",
